        "text": "Only take heed — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Their only danger was, lest they should grow careless and unmindful of all the wonderful things that God had done for them; for which reason he would have every Israelite to make these weighty concerns the subject of his most frequent study and intense meditation. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Especially the day — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "When God delivered the law from mount Sinai to them, with such awful appearances of divine majesty. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thou stoodest — S",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "ome of them stood there in their own persons, though then they were but young; the rest in the loins of their parents.",
